etymologies: late 16th century (in the sense ‘having magnitude or spatial extent’): from medieval Latin quantitativus, from Latin quantitas (see quantity)

definitions: relating to, measuring, or measured by the quantity of something rather than its quality
shortDefinitions: relating to, measuring, or measured by quantity of something rather than its quality

definitions: denoting or relating to verse whose meter is based on the length of syllables, as in Latin, as opposed to the stress, as in English.
shortDefinitions: denoting or relating to verse whose metre is based on length of syllables, as in Latin, as opposed to stress
